title: Ballinacor North
text:
Ballinacor North () is a <a href="Barony%20%28Ireland%29">barony</a> in <a href="County%20Wicklow">County Wicklow</a>, <a href="Republic%20of%20Ireland">Republic of Ireland</a>.
Etymology.
Ballinacor North derives its name from the Ballinacor Castle. (from Irish "Baile na Corra", town of the weir).
Location.
Ballinacor North is located in central <a href="County%20Wicklow">County Wicklow</a>, in the <a href="Wicklow%20Mountains">Wicklow Mountains</a>.
History.
Ballinacor North: the <a href="O%27Byrne%20family">O'Byrne</a> (Ó Broin) sept, originally of Kildare, were centred near here after the 12th century and included the territory of Gabhal Raghnaill.
 The original Ballinacor barony was divided into north and <a href="Ballinacor%20South">south</a> in 1798.
